  "abstract": "INTRODUCTION There is a continuing need to increase food production as the world population is expected to exceed 6 billion by 2050. In both the developed and undeveloped countries, the cost for achieving production has become too high because of the need to incur costs for controlling insect pests that cause an estimated loss of $10 billion annually....",
